body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to Miller Auto Solutions. My name is Dennis Miller. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hi, my name is Andrea Adams.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Andrea. Can you please provide me your date of birth?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's September seventeen, nineteen eighty-five.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Andrea. Could you also tell me the last four digits of your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Yes, it's eight nine seven six.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that information. If you have any further questions or concerns, feel free to let me know.

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Thank you, I appreciate your assistance.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Andrea. Thank you for your time and have a wonderful day.
